Sentencas: The effects of Sr substitution on the crystal chemistry, phase stability, and electrochemical performance as cathodes in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) of the layered LnBa(1-x)Sr(x)CoCuO(5+delta) (Ln = Nd and Gd) perovskites have been investigated.
Titulo: Layered LnBa1-xSrxCoCuO5+δ (Ln = Nd and Gd) perovskite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The LnBa(1-x)Sr(x)CoCuO(5+delta) oxides crystallize in tetragonal P4/mmm symmetry for 0 <= x <= 0.75.
Titulo: Layered LnBa1-xSrxCoCuO5+δ (Ln = Nd and Gd) perovskite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The x = 0.75 samples show a significant improvement in electrochemical performance compared to the x = 0 samples for both Ln = Nd and Gd.
Titulo: Layered LnBa1-xSrxCoCuO5+δ (Ln = Nd and Gd) perovskite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In an electrolyte (La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.8)-supported single cell configuration (thickness = 0.50 mm), the Ln = Gd series shows an improved maximum power density from 468 mW cm(-2) for the Sr-free (x = 0) sample to 530 mW cm(-2) for the x = 0.75 sample.
Titulo: Layered LnBa1-xSrxCoCuO5+δ (Ln = Nd and Gd) perovskite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In the Ln = Nd system, the x = 0.75 sample shows a maximum power density of 562 mW cm(-2).
Titulo: Layered LnBa1-xSrxCoCuO5+δ (Ln = Nd and Gd) perovskite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The Sr substitution was found to have negligible effect on the thermal expansion coefficients (TEC) between the x = 0 and x = 0.75 samples in both series.
Titulo: Layered LnBa1-xSrxCoCuO5+δ (Ln = Nd and Gd) perovskite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
